com.broudy.gcm.control.repos

Class BeanRepository<DTO extends AbstractDTO>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.broudy.gcm.control.repos.BeanRepository<DTO>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CitiesRepository, CreditCardsRepository, MapsRepository, PurchasesRepository, SitesRepository, ToursRepository, UsersRepository

    public abstract class BeanRepository<DTO extends AbstractDTO>
extends java.lang.Object
    An abstract repository-like class for convenience and re-usability considerations. Each repository will have a bean, a list of beans, and a super bean.

    Created on the 5th of June, 2019.

    Author:
    Julian Broudy

    • Constructor Detail

      • BeanRepository

        BeanRepository(DTO theDTO)
        Constructs the basis of any DTORepository. Initializes the bean's property and the superBean with the passed dto as well as initializes beansList. Constructor calls setupInitialBean(C) and startInternalInitialization().
        Parameters:
        theDTO - the initial Renderable to initialize this repository with.

    • Method Detail

      • startInternalInitialization

        protected abstract void startInternalInitialization()
        This is the last method called from within the BeanRepository(DTO) constructor.

      • setupInitialBean

        protected abstract <C extends DTO> void setupInitialBean(C theDTO)
        This method is called from within the BeanRepository(DTO) constructor. It is used to initialize subclasses' private specific DEFAULT_DTO with the theDTO passed to the constructor.
        Parameters:
        theDTO - is the passed DTO that would be set as the specific DEFAULT_DTO in subclass.
